$ Excel: Data -> Outline

The following three functions allow to *collapse* and later *expand* rows/columns:
  • Group
  • Ungroup
  • Subtotal

Show/Hide Detail

{ Settings (in the bottom right corner)

  Tick or untick
    • Summary rows below detail
    • Summary columns to right of detail
    • Automatic styles

  Buttons:
    • Create
    • Apply Styles
    • Ok/Cancel

  It seems that this settings link is deactivated if the active cell is within the area containing excels data (i. e. the area that gets selected with `ctrl-A`).

}
